# Research
## Transisters: BJTs and MOSFETs  

The latter is prevalent in digital electronics for reasons of performance, cost, and scale.   
The former is common *depending on the application* due to concerns with power consumption, heat, and noise.   

Sources: 
[MOSFET Advantages Over BJT's] https://www.quora.com/Why-is-MOSFET-preferred-over-a-transistor
[Technical Differentiation between BJT and FETs](https://www.quora.com/What-is-the-different-between-BJT-and-mosfet-transistor)

## Underlying Physics

Transistor innerworkings are founded on chemistry, surprisingly. 


